Senior Chinese diplomat Wang Yi on Saturday made clear China's solemn position on the so-called airship incident in an informal conversation with U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken. Wang, director of the Office of the Foreign Affairs Commission of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, met with Blinken on the sidelines of the ongoing 59th Munich Security Conference at the request of the U.S. side. Wang, also a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, urged the U.S. side to change course, acknowledge and repair the damage that its excessive use of force caused to China-U.S. relations. (Cover: Wang Yi, director of the Office of the Foreign Affairs Commission of the CPC Central Committee, speaks at the Munich Security Conference, Munich, Germany, February 18, 2023. /Chinese Foreign Ministry)